61.1	Yusuf_al-Qaradawi	Yusuf al-Qaradawi	Yusuf al-Qaradawi (Arabic: â€Ž; born September 9, 1926) is a controversial Egyptian Islamic theologian. He is best known for his programme, ash-Shariah wal-Hayat ("Shariah and Life"), broadcast on Al Jazeera, which has an estimated audience of 60 million worldwide. He is also well known for IslamOnline, a popular website he helped found in 1997 and for which he now serves as chief religious scholar.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Qardawi.JPG/220px-Qardawi.JPG
